          "$type": "text",
          "text": "{\"week_number\":1,\"phase_type\":\"Base\",\"weekly_target_km\":62,\"is_deload_week\":false,\"days\":[{\"day_of_week\":0,\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"LongRun\",\"notes\":\"24 km easy long run at 5:04–5:34/km. Keep effort conversational throughout — this is aerobic foundation work, not a test. Aim for the slower end of the range if legs feel heavy from last week.\"},{\"day_of_week\":1,\"slot_type\":\"Rest\",\"workout_type\":null,\"notes\":\"Full rest or gentle walking only. Monday recovery is a key part of making Sunday's long run count.\"},{\"day_of_week\":2,\"slot_type\":\"CrossTrain\",\"workout_type\":\"CrossTrain\",\"notes\":\"Optional 30–45 min low-impact cross-training (cycling, swimming, yoga). Keep heart rate easy. This is active recovery, not a fitness session.\"},{\"day_of_week\":3,\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"notes\":\"10 km easy at 5:04–5:34/km. Mid-week aerobic maintenance. No pressure on pace — just accumulate time on feet.\"},{\"day_of_week\":4,\"slot_type\":\"Rest\",\"workout_type\":null,\"notes\":\"Rest day. You're building toward a big training block — protecting Thursday keeps Friday quality high.\"},{\"day_of_week\":5,\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"Tempo\",\"notes\":\"12 km total: 3 km warm-up at easy pace, 6 km at threshold pace (4:12/km), 3 km cool-down. This mirrors your recent tempo work — you've shown you can handle this load well.\"},{\"day_of_week\":6,\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"notes\":\"16 km easy at 5:04–5:34/km. Saturday medium-long run builds aerobic volume without taxing the system. Stay aerobic — this is not a tempo effort.\"}],\"week_summary\":\"Welcome to Week 1 of your marathon build, Priya. Your recent training shows real consistency — a 26 km long run, solid tempo work, and marathon-pace sessions all in the past two weeks. That's a strong foundation to build from. This opening week sits at 62 km, just a touch above your current 60 km base, keeping us within safe progression while establishing the four-day structure that fits your schedule. The focus this week is aerobic volume and rhythm: a long run Sunday, a quality tempo Friday, and two easy runs to fill out the week. Every easy kilometre you run at the right pace is an investment in the aerobic engine that will carry you to 3:15 in September.\"}"
        }
      ]
